column5: I dropped the kids off at school and went to pick AverageJoeFishing to hit the Sturgeon River.  We were on the water by 09:00... bite was kind of slow today and the wind was a bit swift as was the current...we managed 10 Walleye and kept 7 averaging at 14"  With the occasional "hand sized" Rock Bass and a few Smallies..  All in all It was a great day.       Not bad for fishing in Downtown Sturgeon Falls.  Randy
Nice job guys! Now it's time to get beer for that beer batter.
NOt bad indeed!!!  Definitely the right way to kick off the long weekend
Awesome Randy What time is supper again Thanks for sharing Leechman
Well done boys.  I have recorded all of the back ground shots in my memory banks for future trips. I guess I'll have to gety out with "Randy the guide" Who gets 4 fish to take home?
Thanks for the report! I need to get myself a walleye, never caught one before!
Looks like a very nice day spent with a fellow OFC'er. Enjoy the feed. Yummy!
Ummmm...walleye. Hopefully I can get into some tomorrow.  Enjoy your supper!
Always fun to catch some walleye right in town Especially when fishing with a great fishing partner eh randy? lol

Walleye & Shrimp  on the Barbie tomorrow night, Stuffed Peppers, Mushrooms & Onions...Potato Wedge pouches...Side Pork and Rolled Loin Steaks.....and cold sides...MMMMM (Homer Drooling Emoticon) ....should be good...actually better than the Sunday Turkey.  Thanks, AverageJoeFishing ,for your share of the catch.   Randy
That's alot of fun when you jog those up.  That dinner sounds good to
